# Coach Trip Booking Flow — Naming Conventions & Architecture

## Overview

All code related to the coach trip (xe khách) booking flow must use `Trip`, `_trip`, `trip_`, or `Trip_` prefixes/suffixes to avoid naming conflicts with the existing `tour` booking flow. This rule applies to all files, classes, variables, functions, and folders under `lib/ui/user/trip/` and `lib/data/services/trip/`.

## Naming Conventions

| Entity | Convention | Example |
|--------|-----------|---------|
| Folder/Feature | `trip_*` or `_trip_` | `lib/ui/user/trip/home/`, `lib/ui/user/trip/booking_input/` |
| Screen | `*_screen.dart` with `Trip` prefix | `trip_home_screen.dart`, `trip_list_screen.dart` |
| ViewModel | `*_view_model.dart` with `Trip` prefix | `trip_home_view_model.dart`, `trip_list_view_model.dart` |
| Model | `trip_*_data.dart` | `trip_seat_data.dart`, `trip_booking_data.dart` |
| Service | `trip_*_service.dart` | `trip_service.dart`, `trip_service_impl.dart` |
| Repository | `trip_*_repository.dart` | `trip_booking_repository.dart` |
| Variable/Field | `trip_*` or `_trip` | `tripService`, `_tripList` |
| Route constants | `trip*` | `tripHome`, `tripList`, `tripBookingDetail` |
| State/Enum | `Trip*` or `trip*` | `TripPaymentState`, `tripStatus` |

